Source:  Loughnan Glossary
Author:  LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page:  8
Edition:
Quote:  bloom: Grey to yellow-grey tint produced by the presence of the abundant wool grease typical of a very healthy sheep. Though this practice is now disallowed, such colour was sometimes sprayed on when preparing sheep for the show-ring.
